TextEng: Not soon enough, in my opinion.
A good friend? Who are you kidding?
Spit it out.
That I would get you some of this wine?
Text: 그 와인 좀 구해 달라는 거?

TextEng: I'll see what I can do.
I should go.
I'd like to see what you have for sale.
Forget it. I have better things to do than "hooking you up".
Text: 됐어. 너한테 '술 구해다 주는' 것보다 할 일이 많아.

TextEng: <StartAction>[Sigh.]</Start> Fine, fine. I'll look into it.
What's in it for me if I get this wine for you?
Text: 그 와인 구해 주면 나한테 뭐가 좋은데?

TextEng: And just how would I get you this wine?
Maybe it's time you slowed down on the drinking, Torias.
Text: 술 좀 줄일 때 된 것 같은데, 토리아스.

TextEng: Fine, fine. Drink away... what do I care?
Text: 좋아, 좋아. 실컷 마셔... 내가 알 바 아니지.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> I'm concerned about you, Torias, that's all.
No, not really.
Yes, I am.
Congratulations.
I'll believe it when I see it.
Sounds great.
What makes you think we're friends?
Of course, I'll do whatever I can.
What do you want, Torias?
Out with it.
I guess I will, at that.
We might meet each other again.
What's the problem?
I said no and I meant it.
Not really.
No, not yet.
No, and I don't intend on looking, either.
I have a bottle right here, in fact.
Sure. Hit me.
